In this article, President Donald Trump addresses the tragic shooting that occurred at a country music concert in Las Vegas, Nevada. He expresses his sadness, shock, and grief over the incident and condemns the act of violence as an act of pure evil. The President acknowledges the efforts of the Las Vegas Metropolitan Police Department and first responders in quickly responding to the situation and preventing further loss of life. He offers prayers and support to the families of the victims and wishes a full and speedy recovery to the wounded. The President announces that he will be visiting Las Vegas to meet with law enforcement, first responders, and the families of the victims. He emphasizes the unity and strength of the American people in times of tragedy and calls upon the bonds that unite them. The President concludes by expressing his belief that even in the darkest times, a single light of hope can bring brightness and that the nation will find unity and peace in the face of evil.